tkissing would make them see otherwise. So I don't see how &quot;asking for permission&quot; essentially is going to make any difference. <br>  <br> /sigh this just seems to be a never ending debate, one that will never be remedied. I guess all that we can hope for is for things to go along as they are. For the most part guild A and B aren't warring all the time, and although there are disagreements at times Povar seems to be pretty good. <br>  <br> One last thing to think on.. Povar is OUR server, it may be owned by Verant but its what WE as a collective make it. Unless everyone is willing to see that and start to work together, all is a lost cause. As I stated before since every guild has someone that reads these boards, appoint someone to be that person to check. Not everyone's going to like it but perhaps it will save some toe-stepping in the future. Verant may not support a reservation system (which someone made a point yesterday that its more of a &quot;wish to do zone X&quot; system which I like better) but it has become an acceptable standard by MOST people on this server save a few main guilds.. so be it.. but if we all can't start getting along Povar is going to become a living hell for everyone. <br>  <br> Just my 2cp worth.. which isn't much in the face of most people apparently. <br>  <br> 
