			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				You made a good point or two Anax, even though your choice of words makes me bristle.  I am not a noob, nor a whiner...however, I think the same system the bigger guilds used to enforce (the talk to us and if we feel like it we will race you to it...which at least one of your guild members has admitted happened in the past) is just as flawed as the reservation system, but in different ways.  First off the racing leads to a competitiveness that can only lead to whining and bitching when Guild A steps on Guild B's toes.  I agree with talking to the other guilds about plans and that settling your problems that happen in game on this board is probably not the way to go, but I also feel that at least one or two of the guilds don't have any respect for anyone who isn't a big name.  And vice versa...many of the smaller guilds have very little respect for bigger guilds for past &quot;crimes&quot; that were committed.  I have heard the bigger guilds respond to posts with &quot;And you are?&quot;  Wow, that is a mature way to handle a post...so if you don't know me, my opinion doesn't matter.  Well, personally that is bullshit.  It is also bullshit on the part of the smaller guilds to automatically say &quot;Oh, the big guilds are out to get us, so lets get them first.&quot;  And believe me I have seen that happen and have know of at least one guild on our server that cheered when a member of Harmonium got kill stole from in Sol A when she was messing around with her low level character.  That is just as wrong.  The biggest problem on our server is that we stopped working together as a server.  Instead, way too many people have the &quot;Uber&quot; vs. &quot;Small Guild&quot; attitude.  All the small guilds feel that the uber guilds think they are better than everyone else.  And heck, I would think that too if I used this board as my only source of knowledge.  There are some arrogant jerks who represent their guilds on this board.  However, I have dealt with the bigger guilds, joked about Bayerithe being a fashion no-no, and helped people who in turned helped me at times.  These guilds are full of individuals.  Some of the uber-guild members view all others as noobs...this is just as wrong as the small guilds thinking everyone is a jerk in an uber-guild.  Smaller guilds may not have the same numbers as the uber-guilds, but they are just as entitled to the fun places as the uber-guilds.  They may fail miserably and if they do they don't deserve to be berated for it as I have seen on this board...because hell at least they are trying and not sitting in the Butcherblocks killing dwarf guards for xp and not learning how dungeons/planes work.  There is no solution to this problem, because everyone is looking for the littlest slight to point out and say &quot;Hey look they are bad guys.&quot;  Things will continue on Povar, and we will just have to wait and see how ugly things become before a solution is worked out that at least 95% of the people are happy with.  (yeah right, like that will ever happen.) <br>  <br> Sorry for my rambling, but I am really tired of this debate becoming the &quot;weak guilds&quot; vs. the &quot;strong guilds.&quot; because that never even should have been the reason for the dissention in the first place. <br>  <br> Lathir <br> Blue Rose Order		

