				Anax, a couple issues. <br>  <br> I generally actually agree with those who say the reservation system isn't good. I personally don't like it, although NA will continue posting INTENTIONS to do a certain raid. There's nothing wrong with intentions.  <br>  <br> I'd hope that people from Harm, Triton, NA, Aquilo, Riding Insanity, or WHOEVER would check up here or over at Heather's page, and read someone's intention to go do a certain place and honor that. <br>  <br> Unfortunately, that doesn't always happen. <br>  <br> I think its amusing that Harmonium members always are proponents of in-game communication, and that's fine. However, I have a feeling if I wanted to lead an NA attempt on Venril Sathir, and give Baven (sorry, Nenja) a tell stating our intention, he'd do nothing but laugh in my face. <br>  <br> I also wouldn't be suprised if he, Zaar, or &lt;insert big guildleader here&gt; would react in this same way to a smaller guild saying &quot;Hey, we plan on doing Fear tomorrow could you please stay out of our way&quot;. That's why in-game communication doesn't work as well. <br>  <br> That said, to anyone feeling entitled to a zone because you posted on a board, you're completely wrong. This is a tool that helps raids, but by no means does it entitle you to JACK SHIT. <br>  <br> And to all you newer high levels that are in smaller guilds trying to do this shit, and you think people like Zaar and Baven are spawns of the devil himself, realize that I've seen BOTH of them help out many a smaller guild on many, many situations. Giving pointers on how to take out Vox.. helping people who have Fear breaks go massively wrong get their gear back, you name it. As much as both of them can be hard asses sometimes.. they've also done a lot to help many many people out. They'll be ridiculed one day, praised the next.. unfortunately people have a short memory when it comes to the good things and only remember the bad things. <br>  <br> Oh by the way, Harmonium will be recieving some in-game communication soon from NA to work out either taking Venril out, or Severilous. If you guys are a proponent of using in-game communication to work things like this out. we'll soon see if you're blowing smoke or not. If you are blowing smoke, I think it will be a bit harder to push guilds like NA, RA, and Triton around as it will be with smaller guilds. <br>  <br>  <br>  <br>  <br> 		

